	(text "Buck-boost Regulator"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 313.69 148.082 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "6db7e69f-e699-4b91-b792-20641cdf1fee")
	)
	(text " Area                  | Note                                                                                                                             \n --------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- \n Input rail            | SYS_RAW feeds TPS63900 VIN. Do not connect TPS63900 input to VIN_SOLAR.                                                          \n Input cap placement   | C5 10µF is the TPS63900 input capacitor. Place close to U3 VIN/GND. Keep it even though BQ24074 also has C4 on SYS_RAW    \n Output rail meaning   | 3V3_SYS is the regulated 3.3V system rail. It powers STM32, sensors, and logic pullups                                 \n Output cap placement  | C6 22µF is the TPS63900 output capacitor. Place close to U3 VOUT/GND                                                            \n Inductor              | L1 2.2µH connects only between LX1 and LX2. Use a shielded power inductor, not a signal inductor                              \n Switching nodes       | LX1/LX2/L1 are noisy high-speed switching nodes. Keep traces short and away from RF, antenna, crystals, and sensitive ADC lines\n EN pin                | EN tied to SYS_RAW means the regulator turns on whenever charger/battery power is available                               \n Future enable control | EN is the future control point if we later add ship-mode, magnetic wake, or undervoltage supervisor                                                          \n Output voltage config | CFG3=16.2kΩ sets VO(1)=3.3V when SEL=GND                                                                                        \n Alternate config path | CFG1=36.5kΩ and CFG2=0Ω configure the alternate SEL=HIGH path as 3.3V as well                                                   \n 0Ω resistor           | R9 0Ω is intentional. It is a configuration resistor, not a normal load resistor                                                \n Power pad             | U3 EP must connect to GND plane with vias. U3 GND pin still needs a normal GND connection                                      \n Capacitor type        | Use ceramic X5R/X7R caps. Prefer voltage rating with margin, e.g. 10V for SYS_RAW input cap                                    \n Layout priority       | Place U3, L1, C5, and C6 as a tight cluster. The regulator layout matters more than schematic neatnes                                                        "
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 302.006 200.914 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(face "Adwaita Mono")
				(size 0.762 0.762)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "7ffed4f8-5ac8-4b4d-8e5d-4474e9a46741")
	)
	(text " Area                | Note                                                                                                                                  \n ------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- \n Main MCU rail       | `3V3_SYS` powers STM32 `VDD`, `VDDSMPS`, `VDDRF`, and `VBAT`.                                                                         \n Supply requirement  | STM32WL55 supply must stay within `1.8V-3.6V`; never connect MCU supply pins to `BAT_RAW`, `SYS_RAW`, or `VIN_SOLAR`.                 \n VDDA rail           | `VDDA` is derived from `3V3_SYS` through `R14 0Ω`. Keep `VDDA` as a separate net for analog filtering.                                \n VDDA filter         | `R14` default is `0Ω`. It can later be replaced with a ferrite bead if analog noise is an issue.                                      \n VDDA caps           | `C8 1µF` and `C9 10nF` must be on the `VDDA` side of `R14`, close to STM32 `VDDA` pin 41.                                             \n Internal SMPS       | `VLXSMPS → L2 15µH → SMPS_1V55`; `VFBSMPS` and `VDDRF1V55` connect to `SMPS_1V55`.                                                    \n SMPS cap            | `C7 470nF` connects `SMPS_1V55` to GND. Place close to `VFBSMPS/VDDRF1V55/VSSSMPS`.                                                   \n SMPS net meaning    | `SMPS_1V55` is the STM32 internal SMPS output. Do not use it as a general-purpose system rail.                                        \n VDDPA selector      | `JP_PA_SEL` selects the PA supply for `VDDPA` pin 25.                                                                                 \n PA low-power mode   | `JP_PA_SEL 1-2 bridged`: `VDDPA = SMPS_1V55`, for low-power PA / `RFO_LP`.                                                            \n PA high-power mode  | `JP_PA_SEL 2-3 bridged`: `VDDPA = 3V3_SYS`, for high-power PA / `RFO_HP`.                                                             \n PA selector warning | Never bridge both sides of `JP_PA_SEL`; this would short `SMPS_1V55` to `3V3_SYS`.                                                    \n RF path warning     | Changing `JP_PA_SEL` is not enough for high-power TX. RF output path must also use `RFO_HP`, not `RFO_LP`.                            \n Decoupling caps     | Add 100nF close to each main supply pin: `VDD pin 11`, `VDD pin 44`, `VDDSMPS pin 46`, `VDDRF pin 28`.                                \n Bulk cap            | `C14 4.7µF` connects `3V3_SYS` to GND near the MCU as local bulk capacitance.                                                         \n Grounding           | `VSSSMPS` and exposed pad `EP` must connect to GND. EP should connect to the ground plane with vias.                                  \n Net check           | `3V3_SYS`, `VDDA`, and `SMPS_1V55` must be separate schematic nets except through their intended components.                          \n RF TODO             | `VR_PA`, `RFO_LP`, `RFO_HP`, `RFI_P`, and `RFI_N` belong to the RF matching/antenna section and are not finished in this power block. \n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 30.48 122.682 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(face "Adwaita Mono")
				(size 0.762 0.762)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "9109aad2-7321-4cc7-9c89-da417f5c8676")
	)
	(text " Area            | Note                                                                                        \n --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- \n HSE32 placement | Place the 32 MHz crystal close to `OSC_IN/OSC_OUT`, with short symmetric traces.            \n LSE32 placement | Place the 32.768 kHz crystal close to `PC14/PC15`.                                          \n Clock layout    | Keep crystal traces away from buck-boost, STM32 SMPS, RF output path, and antenna matching. \n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 22.352 176.022 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(face "Adwaita Mono")
				(size 0.762 0.762)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "b193f917-b2d8-47d4-82d9-377fc8853cd1")
	)
	(text "Area  | Note\n------|--------------------------------------\nD1    | low-leakage TVS, place close to J1\nC1/C2 | place close to solar charger VIN/GND"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 332.994 50.8 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(face "Adwaita Mono")
				(size 0.762 0.762)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "c3ef21ce-adc3-4be3-8bb3-d07e3945481c")
	)
